flexflux.applications

Class FlexfluxCompFVA

  • java.lang.Object
    • flexflux.applications.FFApplication
      • flexflux.applications.FlexfluxCompFVA

  • public class FlexfluxCompFVA
extends FFApplication

    Compares the results of two FVA analyses given a metabolic network, an objective function and two different set of constraints.

    An FVA analysis consists in getting the optimal value for the objective function, setting this value as a constraint and, given a list of entities, minimize and maximize their values. If no entity is specified in argument -e, the FVA analysis is performed on all reactions.
    Author:
    lmarmiesse 6 mars 2013
